"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Szkt94xkWR3J36wEBTZoSg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I came here for dinner my first day in Geneva.  Since prices for food everywhere around here hurt the wallet, I opted for a mixed salad with a single portion of raclette.    Still overpriced, but slightly less pricy than the 25 franc/per person fondue for two. <br><br>The salad was good and has a simple thin tangy dressing with carrot, tomato, cucumber and lettuce.  The raclette was even better...a small plate of thick melted cheese served with small pickled onions, cornichons and a big basket of hot fingerling potatoes.  An unusual combination, but delicious nonetheless.<br><br>My husband had a smoked duck salad with bits of orange and gruyere.  The duck was sparse but he still enjoyed it.  But 21 francs?  Eek.  Apparently I&#39;m still not over the price shock here.  <br><br>Anyway, service was great, very nice.  Our server spoke decent English too, so that was great.  He seated us in the front area of the restaurant where they seemed to seat all English speakers.  <br><br>Another note, if you&#39;re looking for wine by the glass, ask for their wine list, because it&#39;s tucked away towards the back of the book.  I had a nice glass of a Johanneisburg white that wasn&#39;t too pricey.  All in all I&#39;d say I&#39;d come back because I do still want to try their fondue!",
