"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Le Opera Bouffe, has to be with out a doubt one of the best kept secrets of Geneva. <br><br>Lets begin with the decorations... you walk in to find cherubs sitting on the book shelves on the walls, with old paints and prints along with old wooden tables and fireplace making you feel you are almost walking into someones home to have dinner.<br><br>The drink selection is fantastic and credit to the special beers they have every now and then. Once the tough choice of food is out of the way, you can then move on to chosing what to have from the ever changing menu. It&#39;s great, not once I have been has the menu been the same. Small, well priced for the quality... there is nothing to fault with this place.<br><br>The food takes a while to prep, but thats is because it is all fresh ingredients and cooked in a &#39;home cooked style&#39;. the service is always with a smile and the atmosphere is very french/swiss french. Relaxed, enjoy the company you are with and don&#39;t rush anywhere.<br><br>A must for anyone who enjoys good food and friendly staff!",
