"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"My review is for the afternoon tea that is served at Windows.  During the week the tea is from 3-6pm, and on weekends starting at noon.  Be sure to book in advance as this place can get busy.  <br><br>The atmosphere at Windows is perfection. The floor to ceiling windows over looking the Jet D&#39;eau automatically bring a brightness and romance to the spot, even on an overcast day.  The interior is cosy and inviting.<br><br>The afternoon tea is 43 CHF per person, and includes your choice of tea, five finger sandwiches, scones w/ double Gruyere creme and heated homemade jam, and a variety of bite sized scrumptious sweets.  This is definitely not a light meal, thankfully I did not have any lunch beforehand, and I didn&#39;t eat much for dinner that evening.  I was stuffed.  You could easily share the one tea between two people.  It is served on a beautiful multi tiered silver tray.  The tea menu is quite large, and there are many interesting selections to choose from.   <br><br>The tea was amazing, and the food was scrumptious.  The scones come out fresh from the oven.  They were the best scones I have had!  I would come back just for a pot of tea and their menu option of a plate of 3 scones served with the creme and  jam.  They were by far the highlight of the entire selection.<br><br>The service was OK.  However, our waitress at the end had ended her shift, and we never seemed to get anyone else after that, so it took a bit to flag someone down at the end.  <br><br>I am glad that I had dressed nicely, as everyone in the restaurant was wearing business suits.  I would have definitely felt out of place in jeans and a t-shirt.",
