"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/rGaAP8vyvTlk29UwDRgq_g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Pauly&#39;s is located in a fantastic historical building that was previously occupied by a cafe that I visited once (good food - but too pricey for lunch).  I had been sad to hear the old place had closed as I really loved the ambiance of the space and had meant to go back to eat there.  After reading John G&#39;s review I didn&#39;t realise that Pauly&#39;s was in the same space - huge bonus!  This place has only been open since September, and they are still working things out. For example, the menu is ever changing, and they are in the process of obtaining a credit card machine - so be sure to bring cash in the short term.  The owners were extremely friendly, and spoke English!  They even had a good Swiss wine selection - reds from Dardagny - cool!  <br><br>My friend and I ordered different beef burgers.  They come medium rare- no pink (unless you ask differently).  Salad and fries are included in the price. The burgers come either junior or large size.  They rave about their milkshakes, but if you are from the US don&#39;t get too excited, these are Swiss style milkshakes which typically are warm and taste like milk with some flavouring.  However, this was the best Swiss style milkshake I have had.  It is actually cold and was well flavoured. My friend from France agreed with me that this was the typical European style milkshake, but that it was very tasty.<br><br>I found that overall my experience here was comparable to Inglewood.  The salad was better here, the fries equivalent, and the burger tasty. However, the bun is better at Inglewood.  Prices about the same as well.  There is more seating for larger groups here than at Inglewood, and they also have steaks and mixed drinks.  I also loved that they have a  foos ball table and free wifi.  <br><br>I took some pics of the current menu as the website doesn&#39;t have it.  You can even order to take away if you need to. <br><br>Warning: the website requires quicktime and is a bit overwhelming - as if pac man and mario took speed.",
