"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4jTuOmeYM0CDGhy58OwShQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"This is the second time I have eaten lunch at La Plancha.  The first time was during the summer when the weather was warm, and they offered a nice outdoor seating area under a canopy.  This time, was my first time inside.  Inside, the restaurant area is small, and has a modern, trendy vibe.  The menu&#39;s are an interesting mix of coat hanger meets glass.  The food both times was good, but didn&#39;t pass the price to quality test that I have in Switzerland.  It&#39;s a given, eating out in Switzerland is pricier than most are used to, but, is the food worthy of the price?  This place didn&#39;t pass that test.  The first time I was here, I saw everyone ordering the burger.  It looked amazing, but I couldn&#39;t bring myself to pay over 30 francs for a burger.  This time, I gave in, and had high hopes, since the presentation of the food on the plate is fantastic.  But, I am not paying for food art, in the end, our taste buds and stomachs have the final vote.  So what was the final word from the senses?<br><br>Smell - Yummy<br><br>Eyes -  Patiently watched everyone else get their beautifully presented plates of food, and waited for a bit too long to finally see the delicious cheesy burger delivered to them.<br><br>Taste-  Disappointed after all the build up, but the meat was good, and the fries had looked crunchy, but were a tad to soggy.<br><br>Ears - noise level OK at first, but in the midst of the meal they turned on some annoying loud dance club music, which did not encourage my friends and I to stay for an espresso that we had been thinking about ordering.<br><br>Touch - Didn&#39;t like the feel of passing 37 CHF away to the server for only 1 burger and a bottle of coke light.",
