"categorystrlist":"Restaurants,Bars,Music Venues",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7_06Ann-VZHZ4B7urZlmCw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I went there three times though my stay in Geneva, but I tried the &#34;real&#34; restaurant only once at midday for a leaving do. So I&#39;ll start my review with that part.<br><br>I was there with a group of colleague on a Wednesday midday and we had a reservation for eight people, which led us to be seated quite quickly. The menu was a simple sheet of paper (quite strange; but it might change quite often ?).<br><br>Most of us order a tartare (I did not take an additional photo since someone already did a cool one). The price was fairly acceptable to me 17, - CHF. I&#39;m accustomed to Zurich Standards and once again my point of view might be slightly biased. Other people took some sort of quiche for a slightly lower price and were given a mixed salad as a starter.<br><br>We did not wait that long to be served, and the tartare was definitely big enough. It is served with french fries and small piece of white bread. Everything was tasty, couldn&#39;t finish the french fries (I&#39;m not a fan of those anyway, even when they are good).<br>Being a business day we stuck water and shared the bottle among the bills. <br><br>That was my review of the interior on midday (and a rainy one at that), onward to the second option you can have during sunny days : there is an open air bar/restaurant where you can get DYI burgers (midday and evening). You basically order your burger at the counter and you tell the chef the cooking time you desire for the steak, he then gives you the buds and you can fit whatever you want in the burger which include classics like salad, tomato, onion, but also some nifty sauces. You also get some tortilla chips with that. Burger (if I&#39;m not mistaken) cost 14,5 CHF and you can get a beer for around 7,0 CHF as stated by another Yelper, still really reasonable to me.<br><br>They can&#39;t, however give you a bill stating you have given any tip or just that you took a meal. Thus, making it possibly more difficult to get refunded by you expense team (should you have to).<br><br>Quite a good place to go, worth a try !",
