"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"A wonderful place and sight for sore eyes (or bellies) seeking some pure, simple but healthy and local food in Geneva, Switzerland. Don&#39;t know why it is so hard, but other than falafel places, which really don&#39;t quite fit the bill,. this can be hard to find. While one can find wonderful but generally somewhat heavy French or Swiss cuisine, fondue etc., and some good but often expensive though not great Italian food, and a few passable Thai and Indian restaurants, despite multiple visits over years it has been difficult to find farm to table type healthy food that is pure, simple and reasonably priced. And that is a shame given the wonderful quality of Swiss agriculture and the proximity of farms to cities.<br><br>Well, Les mangeurs comes through. A small selection of fresh simple home cooked farm to table food, nice bread and soup, local wines, nice desserts and all very reasonably priced. Also a small selection of lovely groceries, like mushroom pasta from France. Delightful co-owners who do it all. One catch, mostly a lunch place, though open till 8 PM. I had a lovely vegetarian soup, bread and green salad that were just what was needed. The place is simple, unassuming with just a few tables, but honest, healthy, delicious and a welcome find! Enjoy and support.....",
