"reviewcomment":"We went there last Tuesday night for dinner and the place was full - and very lively. The American couple on the table next to us told the chef it was their second consecutive night as the food had been so good the night before - some recommendation. I had a good chat with the chef Maurice who does the rounds after service and he clearly has a passion for what he does and for selecting the best local produce. The service is attentive (if a little overworked) with the sous-chef serving the guests straight from the kitchen. My main course was superb - veal with a type of lentil stew - the flavours were excellent and it made a change from steak frites which remains the speciality of the house. Its a nice place with a history too - photographs on the wall show it much the same in 1945. With quality and service this good its easy to see why you&#39;d need to reserve - even mid week in the credit crunch.",
