"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/QwdpkSHcxA1CdsyO563Ggw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I have been walking by this cute little cafe specialising in Syrian specialities for a couple of months now.  I finally had the opportunity to have a delightful lunch here today with a friend.  I could see this place quickly becoming a five star favourite after additional visits.  They have done a good job of taking a very small space feel inviting and warm.  Their menu changes each day with whatever is freshly made up for the lunch rush.  <br><br>The main plat du jour included a small salad, soup, and meze selection (four different sauces to dip your pita bread in).  The hummus was one of my favourites that I have had in Switzerland so far. All of this for only about 23 CHF.  I highly recommend the mint hot tea made from fresh mint tea leaves. For 10 CHF we shared a small plate of homemade Syrian pastries.  All of which were amazing and full of yummy pistachios.  I loved that they were not too sweet or gooey.  <br><br>The owner was very friendly and spoke perfect English. The service was also amazing and quick.  I will definitely be going back here to try out their Syrian coffee special and other specialities.<br>  <br>The hours are a bit weird so be careful.  They are open Monday - Wednesday 11:30- 15:00.  On Thursday and Friday, they are open 11:30-15:00 and also from 19:00-22:00.  They are closed Saturday and Sunday.  There is no website, but you can reach the owner by email at <a href='mailto:rachaperret@me.com'>rachaperret@me.com</a>.  <br><br>Remember don&#39;t blink or you might pass this gem by.",
