"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is another lunch time favorite. Especially on a cold blustery day, and I feel like having some warm comfort food. This place is a take away Italian sandwich shop. They also offer Italian products to purchase.  It is not just sandwiches though, they also have delicious salads, focaccia, panini, piadine, arancini, soupes, lasagnes, raviolis, and yes - the baguette sandwich.  My favorites are the grilled Italian sandwiches (panini, focaccia, etc) and salads.  The baguette sandwiches are a little to heavy on the bread side, and the baguette bread is a bit tough to chew for me here.  I have always wanted to try the home made lasagna, or ravioli, but haven&#39;t had a chance to yet.  The prices for lunch are also reasonable for the quality and volume of food you receive in return.  This place typically has a line, and it is TINY!!  It is usually busy at lunch time with local business persons.  The owners are Italian and very nice.  They also offer a loyalty punch card - so many lunches and you get the 10th / 9th free.  They also do delivery if  you have an office order with a minimum of 60 chf.  Just a tip, if you ask for vinegar and oil on your salad, be sure to ask for just a little bit, as they pour it on otherwise!!!",
