"reviewcomment":"This mini cafe is underneath the California fitness gym. I am not sure if the little cafe is owned by the gym or not.  There is no where to eat at this place, it take away only here. You enter via a sliding glass door, and then a second glass door.  It is such a tiny spot, with a little glass case displaying their yummy looking lentil and quinoa salads (which I still need to try!), and a tiny kitchen area behind were they make all their own fresh bread, etc.  The sandwiches a bit pricey, on the smallish side, but good.  Today, I finally stopped in for their legume (vegetable) soup.  It was exactly what I was looking for. It was vegetable soup like my grandma used to make it. Fresh cut up veggies in a nice simmering broth.  An ongoing winter special is the daily soup for 10 CHF with a baked veggie pie (tomato or spinach (epinards)).  Plus, surprising, I wasn&#39;t expecting a slice of yummy cheese and a piece of their homemade wheat baguette.  A healthy lunch for a great price!   They also have a window that is open out to the street during the winter.  I think you can actually order from outside on the street when it is nice.  They have some really yummy looking muffins that have been calling my name to try some morning when I am in a hurry and have missed breakfast.",
