"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/PGMDkkWad0Tg5gQSwHUnfA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"This restaurant recently opened and it&#39;s motto is &#34;petit resto entre amis&#34;.  You walk inside and the atmosphere is unique with solid undertones of dark pink.  Thankfully we came early, because even though this place is newer, the word has gotten out, and almost all the tables at noon had been reserved.  There is outdoor seating available as well for a nice sunny day.  If I had written this review within two hours of eating, I would have easily given it four stars. However, when your stomach starts to think it is an Olympic gold metal gymnast soon after eating, you wonder. If I am courageous I will adventure there again, because the taste of the food was very good and the service was friendly, but something just didn&#39;t settle right.  There is no carte (menu) at lunch.  It is whatever the plat du jour is for the day at a nice price of 18 chf.  They highly recommended the quiche which is what my friend and I both took, her with soup, and mine with salad.  Everything reminded me as if it had just been made from my grandma&#39;s kitchen.  The food was fresh and tasty.  One of the best quiches I have had in awhile.  The salad was fantastic, and my friend raved about her soup.  We were already talking about coming again.  It could have just been a bad day for the stomach, which is why I will try again sometime.  So four stars overall, but dinged a star for the after effects.",
