"reviewcomment":"This place is definitively quite something! It&#39;s really two places in one. There is two different part, that almost look like two separate places but with the same staff.<br><br>One is a tea room where people come to smoke &#34;Sheesha&#34; and it seem to be the more popular part of the place.<br><br>Specialized in Moroccan cuisine, the restaurant part is less crowded (at least on the Wednesday night when I was there). I had being dying for a good &#34;tajine&#34;  for a few days and that&#39;s what win me to this place initially. The chicken &#34;tajine&#34; with &#34;citron confit&#34; (preserved lemon) was actually quite good... but 32 swiss francs (which is the same as US at this time) for a tajine is quite steep. Now Geneva is quite an expensive city but still... adding a cheese brick as appetizer, a glass of Moroccan wine and a mint tea did bring the bill for a single person to 63 swiss franc! Now the surprise, they do not accept any kind of card. I didn&#39;t swiss franc and they proposed to accept euro but only at a 1.1 exchange rate (a ripoff). Ended up having to go to an ATM to get swiss francs that I didn&#39;t need otherwise.<br><br>The server was nice but she needed to split her time between the two parts of the place so it was quite slow.<br><br>If you are in Geneva and really must need to eat a tajine then it is a good place... but you have to really want it!",
